==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sauba ant
<hw>Sau"ba ant`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A South
American ant (<spn>Oecodoma cephalotes</spn>) remarkable for having two
large kinds of workers besides the ordinary ones, and for the immense
size of its formicaries. The sauba ant cuts off leaves of plants and
carries them into its subterranean nests, and thus often does great
damage by defoliating trees and cultivated plants.</def><-- a
leaf-cutting ant -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sauce</ent>⟦br⟧
